  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a pot over a low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong>, your <strong>dried thyme</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 20-25 min, stirring frequently, or until the onion has softened and caramelised – these are your <strong>caramelised onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-beef-burger-with-onion-gravy-and-dijon-mayo/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onions are caramelising, slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs, then slice each <strong>potato disc</strong> into matchsticks</p><p>Add the <strong>potato matchsticks</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>matchstick fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-beef-burger-with-onion-gravy-and-dijon-mayo/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>beef mince</strong> in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands are the best way!)</p><p>Shape into 1 patty per person</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-beef-burger-with-onion-gravy-and-dijon-mayo/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat and add your <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and charred</p><p>Set aside until serving, reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-beef-burger-with-onion-gravy-and-dijon-mayo/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once caramelised, reserve <strong>half </strong>the <strong>caramelised onions</strong> in a bowl and set aside (you'll use these later!)</p><p>Return the <strong>remaining caramelised onions </strong>in the pot to the heat with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce thickens to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>onion gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-beef-burger-with-onion-gravy-and-dijon-mayo/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>beef patty[ies]</strong>, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min</p><p>Flip the <strong>patty[ies]</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 5 min further until cooked through and charred (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese </strong>and<strong> </strong>wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-beef-burger-with-onion-gravy-and-dijon-mayo/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, top the beef patty[ies] with the <strong>reserved caramelised onions </strong>and <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 3-4 min further, until the cheese has melted – these are your <strong>cheesy patty[ies]</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> (not a fan of mustard? Just add a little!) and your <strong>mayo </strong>in a bowl – this is your <strong>Dijon mustard mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-beef-burger-with-onion-gravy-and-dijon-mayo/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, spread the <strong>Dijon mustard mayo </strong>over the <strong>toasted brioche base</strong>, then top with a handful of <strong>salad</strong>, a <strong>cheesy patty</strong>,<strong> </strong>a drizzle of <strong>onion gravy</strong> and a <strong>toasted brioche lid</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>onion gravy</strong>, <strong>matchstick fries </strong>and <strong>remaining salad </strong>to the side and drizzle your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>and a little <strong>olive oil </strong>over the salad</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
